<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rare" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rare,</orth> 1) uncommon, not often seen: <cit><quote>were man as r. as phoenix,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 17</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>nothing pleaseth but r. accidents,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.231" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 231</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>we'll have thee, as our --r monsters are, painted upon a pole,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 5.8.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 8, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>lived in court -- which r. it is to do -- most praised,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 47</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) extraordinary; mostly in the sense of excellent, very praiseworthy: <cit><quote>all things r. that heaven's air in this huge rondure hems,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 21.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 21, 7</bibl></cit>. <emph>therefore are feasts so solemn and so r., since, seldom coming,</emph> . . . <bibl n="shak. cym 1.52.5" default="NO" valid="yes">52, 5</bibl>. <cit><quote>makes summer's welcome thrice more wished, more r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.56.14" default="NO" valid="yes">56, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I think my love as r. as any she,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.130.13" default="NO" valid="yes">130, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>whose --st havings made the blossoms dote,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 235" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 235</bibl></cit>. <emph>the --st</emph> (queen) <cit><quote>that e'er came there,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 99</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>two most r. affections,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 75</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>so r. a wondered father,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.123.75" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 123</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the --r action is in 